We used generalized logistic growth model (GLM) to predict excess deaths during the first 4 weeks of 2021. GLM characterizes epidemic growth by estimating (i) the intrinsic growth rate, r (ii) a dimensionless “deceleration of growth” parameter, p and (iii) the final epidemic size, k0. The deceleration parameter modulates the epidemic growth patterns including the sub-exponential growth (0< p < 1), constant incidence (p =0) and exponential growth dynamics (p =1). The GLM model is given by the following differential equation:
